definition: to circle/to go back/to turn around/to answer/to return/to revolve/Hui ethnic group (Chinese Muslims)/time/classifier for acts of a play/section or chapter (of a classic book)

sentences.english: Migrated to the Mediterranean Sea via the Suez Canal (Ref. 5385).
sentences.chinese: 经由苏伊士运河回游到地中海了。

sentences.english: I swim twenty laps every morning before work.
sentences.chinese: 我每天早上上班前都会在游泳池来回游二十趟。

sentences.english: She can swim two lengths of the pool.
sentences.chinese: 她在游泳池里能来回游一趟。

sentences.english: Some fish migrate to this section of water to breed.
sentences.chinese: 一些鱼类回游到此水段来繁殖后代。

sentences.english: The salmon fight their way back up the river to spawn.
sentences.chinese: 鲑鱼奋力回游到河里产卵。

sentences.english: This equipment can make water flow back, thus reducing waste.
sentences.chinese: 这个设备可以使水回游，减少浪费。

sentences.english: I began to swim back, but the beach was too far away.
sentences.chinese: 我开始往回游，但离海滩太远了。

sentences.english: He swam several lengths, pushed along by Daisy's urgent quacking.
sentences.chinese: 在黛西呷呷的督促声中，他在浴盆里来回游了好几趟。

sentences.english: Scientists have studied the migration of fish over long distances.
sentences.chinese: 科学家研究过鱼类远距离回游的现象。

definition: to move about/to go from place to place/roving/mobile
to sail against the current/(fig.) to go against the flow
